# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Malleabite — local environment variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values.
# .env.local is gitignored and never committed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ─── Deepgram (real-time voice STT for Hey Mally overlay) ───────────────────
# Required for high-quality voice mode. Without this, falls back to Web Speech API.
#
# STEP 1 — Get a free API key (200 free hours/month)
#   • Go to https://console.deepgram.com (free account)
#   • Create a project → API Keys → Create a key (scope: "Member" is fine)
VITE_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# ─── Picovoice Porcupine (on-device "Hey Mally" wake word) ───────────────────
# Optional. If absent, the app falls back to the Web Speech API wake word.
#
# STEP 1 — Get a free AccessKey
#   • Go to https://console.picovoice.ai (free account, no credit card)
#   • Copy your AccessKey from the dashboard
VITE_PICOVOICE_ACCESS_KEY=

# STEP 2 — Train a "Hey Mally" custom wake word (~5 minutes)
#   • In Picovoice Console → Wake Word → Create a new model
#   • Name: "Hey Mally"   Language: English
#   • Record 3 voice samples when prompted, then export the .ppn file
#
# STEP 3 — Download the acoustic model (one-time setup)
#   npm run setup:porcupine
#   This downloads porcupine_params.pv (~1.9 MB) to public/ 
#
# STEP 4 — Base64-encode the .ppn file you downloaded in Step 2
#   Windows PowerShell:
#     [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("hey-mally_en_wasm_v3_0_0.ppn"))
#   macOS / Linux:
#     base64 -i hey-mally_en_wasm_v3_0_0.ppn
#   Paste the output below (one long string, no spaces or newlines):
VITE_PICOVOICE_KEYWORD_B64=

# Alternative to B64: serve the .ppn from public/ instead
# Copy hey-mally_en_wasm_v3_0_0.ppn → public/hey-mally.ppn
# then set the path below (leave VITE_PICOVOICE_KEYWORD_B64 empty)
# VITE_PICOVOICE_KEYWORD_PATH=/hey-mally.ppn

# Optional: override the acoustic model path (default: /porcupine-params.pv)
# Only needed if you renamed the file or serve it from a CDN
# VITE_PICOVOICE_MODEL_PATH=/porcupine-params.pv
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ─── Firebase / Google ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (Add your Firebase config vars here — see firebase-and-ai-explanation.txt)
# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
# VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# VITE_USE_BACKEND_GOOGLE_OAUTH=false

# ─── FCM Web Push (Mally Action notifications) ───────────────────────────────
# Required for out-of-app push notifications on web.
#
# STEP 1 — Firebase Console → Project Settings → Cloud Messaging
# STEP 2 — Under "Web Push certificates", click "Generate key pair"
# STEP 3 — Copy the public key (Key pair column) and paste below
VITE_FIREBASE_VAPID_KEY=
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
